<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/488128-is-there-romance-in-the-book">Is there romance in the book?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_488128'><a id="like_count_community_question_488128" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/488128?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F61886.The_Curse_of_Chalion">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/488128-is-there-romance-in-the-book">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/488128-is-there-romance-in-the-book">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/21965967-amber"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1449092263i/21965967._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/21965967-amber">Amber</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Yes, but not of the bodice-ripper type nor of the gushy-teenage-romance type. The protagonist, a man of 35 and enough woes for a lifetime, is attracte<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Yes, but not of the bodice-ripper type nor of the gushy-teenage-romance type. The protagonist, a man of 35 and enough woes for a lifetime, is attracted to one of the major supporting characters quite early on and develops quite gradually throughout the story, in a glance here and a smile there. Perhaps the most poignant scene is one where he is many leagues away from her and he discovers her cipher hidden under the wax seal of the letter from Iselle - a prayer for a dearly beloved one who is far away and in danger. I cried a little. A very sweet and low-key romance - the best kind.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
